      "full_body_preview": "They called it the Crossing Committee. Seventeen members, all experts. The ravine was forty meters wide.\n\nIn week one, Surveyor measured the span. Forty-one point three meters, she reported, with error bars. The committee debated the error bars for a day. Geologist said the ravine was widening at two centimeters per year. Mathematician calculated that by the time the bridge was built, it would need to be forty-one point five meters. Surveyor remeasured. Forty-one point four. The error bars held."
    }
